text: Prazniki () is a small settlement south of Turjak in the Municipality of Velike Lašče in central Slovenia. The entire area is part of the traditional region of Lower Carniola and is now included in the Central Slovenia Statistical Region.Velike Lašče municipal site There is a small Baroque chapel-shrine in the settlement. It was built in the 18th century.Slovenian Ministry of Culture register of national heritage reference number ešd 26296 ==References== ==External links== *Prazniki on Geopedia Category:Populated places in the Municipality of Velike Lašče
